                                         "date":  "2026-05-30T00:55:46Z"
                                     },
                       "message":  "SCENE-SAVE-SOURCE-PATH: true Save (silent overwrite of opened scene)\n\nGive Ctrl+S a real Save: when the editor knows the scene\u0027s source file,\nwrite straight back to it with no dialog; Save-As remains the fallback\nwhen there is no known source. Lifts the Dispatch-2 Save-As-only limit\n(Dispatch 3 of the in-app Save line; predecessor #268).\n\n- editor-shell: add scene_source_path: Option\u003cPathBuf\u003e + with_scene_source_path\n  builder + scene_source_path() accessor. replace_world clears it; the scene\n  branch of handle_open_request commits it on a successful .rge-scene Open\n  (a .rge-project leaves it None — the writer cannot overwrite a project).\n  handle_save_request branches: Some -\u003e silent overwrite (no dialog); None -\u003e\n  Save-As, committing the picked path as the new source on success. All\n  failure / cancel / no-hook / PIE paths no-op (source + is_dirty untouched).\n- rge-editor: --scene seeds scene_source_path only for a *.rge-scene launch\n  (a .rge-project launch stays Save-As) — the pre-exec correction.\n\neditor-shell stays dependency-clean (no new trait/dep; reuses\nSceneSaveDialog / SceneSaveHook). +7 headless tests (open commits /\n.rge-project none, silent-overwrite-bypasses-dialog, Save-As-commits,\nSave-As-failure-no-commit, replace_world-clears, PIE-gated no-op).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
